article.description: Tabb scores 24 as Alabama A&M beats Alcorn St. 73-69
article.headline: Tabb scores 24 as Alabama A&M beats Alcorn St. 73-69
article.linkText: Tabb scores 24 as Alabama A&M beats Alcorn St. 73-69
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. -- Ladarius Tabb had 24 points and nine rebounds to help Alabama A&M hold off Alcorn State 73-69 on Monday night. Rakiya Battle scored 13 points and Tyler Davis had 11 for Alabama A&M (8-16, 7-7 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Nicholas West grabbed 13 rebounds as the Bulldogs held a 37-30 advantage on the glass. Tabb had 10 points in the first half as Alabama A&M led by as many as 12 points. LeAntwan Luckett paced Alcorn State (5-22, 4-11) with 22 points on 7-of-21 shooting. George Thomas and Marquis Vance scored 13 apiece, and Tyrel Hunt added 12. The Braves were held to 22-of-62 shooting (35.5 percent). A Luckett dunk gave Alcorn State its first lead of the second half at 61-60 with 4:41 remaining and Vance's layup cut its deficit to 71-69 with seven seconds left. But Battle hit two free throws a second later to seal it.
